{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Protein EFR3 homologue A (EFR3A) is a component of a phosphatidylinositol 4-kinase (PI4K) complex, composed of PI4KA, EFR3 (EFR3A or EFR3B), TTC7 (TTC7A or TTC7B) and FAM126 (FAM126A or FAM126B) [[cite:PUB00090096]].  This complex is required for the attachment of phosphatidylinositol 4-kinase (PI4K) to the plasma membrane.  EFR3A is palmitoylated at its N terminus, anchoring the protein to the plasma membrane, and probably acts as the membrane-anchoring component in the complex [[cite:PUB00090097]]. In yeast, the Efr3p protein is a main regulator of the Stt4p phosphatidylinositol 4-kinase at contact sites between the endoplasmic reticulum and the plasma membrane [[cite:PUB00090098]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR47766" "PROTEIN EFR3"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Protein EFR3", "short" "EFR3"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 1, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 1151, "taxa" 3067, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 1765, "sets" 0, "proteins" 1765, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 1058}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR039786", :literature {"PUB00090098" {"URL" nil, "issue" "1", "authors" ["Bojjireddy N" "Guzman-Hernandez ML" "Reinhard NR" "Jovic M" "Balla T."], "ISO_journal" "J. Cell. Sci.", "DOI_URL" "https://doi.org/10.1242/jcs.157495", "medline_journal" "J Cell Sci", "title" "EFR3s are palmitoylated plasma membrane proteins that control responsiveness to G-protein-coupled receptors.", "year" 2015, "raw_pages" "118-28", "volume" "128", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 25380825}, "PUB00090096" {"URL" nil, "issue" "1", "authors" ["Baskin JM" "Wu X" "Christiano R" "Oh MS" "Schauder CM" "Gazzerro E" "Messa M" "Baldassari S" "Assereto S" "Biancheri R" "Zara F" "Minetti C" "Raimondi A